{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KTE3rC3Ds5mv1aD1yP5w4C","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**PR created:** https://github.com/backflow-labs/backflow/pull/38\n\n### Changes made:\n\n1. **`internal/models/task.go`** — Added `TaskStatusRecovering = \"recovering\"` constant\n\n2. **`internal/notify/webhook.go`** — Added `EventTaskRecovering = \"task.recovering\"` event type\n\n3. **`internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go`** — Three new methods:\n   - `recoverOnStartup()` — Called at the top of `Start()`, finds orphaned `running`/`provisioning` tasks, transitions them to `recovering`, restores `o.running` counter, and fixes instance `RunningContainers`\n   - `monitorRecovering()` — Added to `tick()` before `monitorRunning()`, inspects containers for recovering tasks and resolves them (promote to running, handle completion, or re-queue to pending)\n   - `requeueRecoveringTask()` — Resets a recovering task to pending, conditionally decrements `o.running` based on whether the task was previously running\n\n4. **`internal/api/handlers.go`** — `DeleteTask` now allows cancelling `recovering` tasks\n\n5. **`internal/orchestrator/recovery_test.go`** — 8 new tests covering all recovery paths\n\n6. **`internal/models/task_test.go`** — Added `TaskStatusRecovering` to non-terminal status assertions\n\n7. **`CLAUDE.md`** and **`docs/schema.md`** — Updated status lifecycles and webhook event documentation"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":400,"cache_read_input_tokens":82537,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":400,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4aa0ce57-5476-4987-a635-a74810c9f869","uuid":"b2b45c29-3eb4-408a-aafa-ab9beca83799"}
